'''Yuri Maier''', ([[Corrientes]], [[Argentina]], April 5, 1989) is an Argentine [[Olympic wrestling|Olympic wrestler]], who has managed many international titles representing his country. Among the most outstanding results, there are a total of 9 medals in [[Pan American Championship]]s in different age groups making it the largest Argentinian medalist in his discipline.
Also he won the Breakthrough Award Clar<U+00ED>n Deportivo in 2004, Jorge Newbery Award 2005 for the best athlete of [[Buenos Aires]] City in his discipline and repeatedly alternated at the best athlete of Argentina.
